abstract: >-
  This technical note introduces the AIKernel Semantic DSL Compiler, an OS-level mechanism for governing probabilistic LLM-generated plans through deterministic compilation rather than direct execution. The model treats LLM-generated plans as non-Turing-complete structured intent, compiles them through formal admissibility checks into governed pipelines, and records execution through ResultStep, SemanticDelta, and hash-linked ReplayLog artifacts.
